inn1.comm: ooh appeared to come back in after landing on a goodish length outside off, left alone to the keeper
this one went the other way, short of a good length and he shoulders arms to that one
in the channel outside off stump, holds its line and it's been left alone to the keeper
a bit wider this time, trying to get him to drive, leaves that alone
on a goodish length outside off again and he lets that one go through
down the leg side, clips the pads as he tries to glance that one down fine, a maiden to begin with
slides that wide of the off stump and that's been left alone to the keeper
lets that one go through again
watches that one go through to the keeper as well
short of a good length and he doesn't make contact again
short of a good length, gets on the back foot and defends that in the direction of cover
two maidens in a row, just outside off and Watling stabs at that one, it leaves the right hander to go through to the keeper
a bit wide this time and Guptill sees that one go through, again
a bit of away swing there and Guptill is still not tempted to drive this one, leaves this be
angling in towards middle, plays it from the crease, taps it down into the leg side

Guptill goes, that one came back in and took Guptill by surprise, banged in short on the off and Guptill tried to sway out of the way but couldn't, played at it, it took the top of the bat and lobbed up towards point, comfortable catch and South Africa have struck early
shortish and that's been knocked down into the on side
swing and on a driving length, Williamson chases it, just goes past the outside edge as he goes for the drive
Tsotso beats the outside edge, held it a little back from a good length and Watling loosely played at that one
shortish on the off, gets back and across to that one and he drops it into the off side
strong punch down the ground and that's a boundary. pitched on a length and he offers a straight bat to push it past mid-off
misfield at mid-on this time, driven soundly off the front foot, well timed and McLaren fumbles as he slides to his left, two more to the score
short of a good length on middle, gets on the back foot and plays it back down the pitch
bowled on a length at 124.8kmph, rocks forward and plays it firmly back to the bowler who stops it on his follow through
short of a good length, gets behind that one nicely and defends it into the leg side
tight line in the channel outside off stump and it's been left alone by Willliamson
shortish on middle, gets on the back foot and plays it on the pitch
short of a good length, crunched off the back foot past the bowler
a touch too straight there, angling in towards middle and that's played past mid-on for three runs, Morkel gives chase
shortish on middle, struck high on the thigh as he tries to work that into the leg side
short of a good length on middle, gets on the back foot and defends it in front of the bowler
slightly short outside off, jabs that one, a half-pull, past mid-on for just a single
slightly short on the off, gets on the back foot and plays it back towards the bowler
lovely timing, goodish length and he just strikes that through the line, cracks it sweetly past the bowler, who doesn't bend low enough to stop that, and beats mid-on
short of a good length, gets back and punches that in the direction of point
slightly short on the off, steps forward and taps it to cover
dropped that short on middle, and he got himself under that one easily in the end
nips back in from outside off and he leaves that one alone to the keeper
finds the gap, pitched up from Kleinveldt and he square-drives that one through point and cover for a boundary, quick outfield
on a length outside off and he pushes that stylishly through the line to mid-off
short of a good length on the off, gets on the back foot and drops that one into the leg side
slightly short, pushes that towards mi-on, thinks of a single but it's not there
short and wide and that's smacked hard but Faf dives to his left to stop that one and save a few runs, applause all around
rocks forward to that one and defends it in the direction of point
width, bowled at 129kmph, Watling goes at it hard but finds Ingram at extra cover
goes at it hard again, wider this time and he wants to cream that through the covers, doesn't make contact
short of a good length, gets on the back foot and defends it to cover
pitched on a length on middle, drives it straight towards mid-on
bowls that one in the channel outside off stump, lets that one through to the keeper
full and wide and he goes after that one, drives hard but can't connect, goes past the outside edge
short of a good length, bowled at 137kmph, gets on the back foot and taps it into the off side
fullish on the off, defends it solidly towards extra cover off the front foot
full on the off, gets front and across and drives it towards mid-on
bowled at 135kmph, pitched up and he slices that one but can't get it past the infield
short, there to hit, Watling goes after it but can't get it past point, struck straight towards him
shortish on the off, punched off the back foot towards point from the crease
drives that on the up but not timed well enough, rolls just as far as mid-off and there's no single on offer
shortish on the off, stabs it towards cover from the crease

run-out appeal, superb fielding at mid-off from Peterson, drives a full delivery towards mid-off, Peterson collects, turns and throws at the stumps, clips the bail but Watling has dived full length and has made it in, he's safe
short of a good length and that's crunched off the back foot towards mid-of
short of a good length,. gets on the back foot and defends it into the leg side
slightly short on the off, rocks back and defends that towards cover
bowled at 144.5kmph, moved forward and across to a short delivery there, and had to fend it away in the end which he managed to do, got a single towards square leg
there was some initial movement across, that was slightly down the leg side and Williamson helped it on its way to the fine-leg boundary, easy release there
well timed but finds mid-on, got across and drove that well, but couldn't get it wide of that fielder
shortish on middle, gets on the back foot and works it through square leg into the deep for a single
The field is still in, goodish length and he's struck it hard but gets it towards cover, not past him, quite a few good shots have gone straight to the fielders
fullish outside off, steers that one towards point, again he can't beat to field
slightly short on the off, nicely done by Williamson, got across there and just punched it between mid-on and midwicket for a couple of runs
wide, too wide, went across and he chased him and slid it wide but Williamson was struggling to reach it
opens the face slightly there and plays it towards point, a packed field on he off side
shortish on the off, guides that one behind point but Smith doesn't allow it to go past him, no single there, slower one from Tsotso
this one is on the pads and Williamson repeats the shot he played against Morkel in the previous over, glides that one towards the fine-leg boundary, gets three this time as Morkel cuts it off
shortish on leg stump, gets a single towards fine leg this time
shortish on the off, gets on top of that one and chops it towards point

trapped in front, Morkel fired that one on a length on off and middle, Watling went across to flick it square, missed it completely and was rapped on the pads right in front, Watling has a word with his partner and decides not to review it, wise call, Morkel has picked up his 100th ODI wicket
fullish outside off and that's been left alone to the keeper
excellent timing from Elliott, pitched up outside off and he's caressed it through the covers for a boundary, came off the meat and sped away
a little wider this time and it's been left alone to the keeper
is welcomed with a boundary, short and wide, too wide and Williamson thrashes it through point, finds the gap through the off side after multiple attempts, for a boundary
and does so again, pitched on a length and he drives it neatly past a diving extra cover to collect consecutive fours
goodish length, gets across and defends it towards the bowler
shortish on the off, gets on the back foot and taps it into the off side
three in the over, lovely drive, the best of the lot, pitched up and he leans forward and just eases into that narrow gap between mid-off and extra cover
change of pace, slower one from McLaren and it's driven straight to mid-off
in the channel outside off stump, keeps its line and he lets that one go through
short of a good length and he shoulders arms to that one
slides it on middle and leg and he clips it down to fine leg for a single
short, played it well, got back and he played it down in front of the bowler
pitched up on the off, drives it straight towards mid-on
short of a good length on the off, rocks on the back foot and plays it down the pitch
McLaren bowls that in the channel outside off and Elliott sees that through to the keeper
fullish outside off, he slices that one in the direction of third man for a single

straight down the ground, Tsttso could have done a better job there as he dived to his left, pitched up and that was nicely driven down the ground, Tsotso ran to his left from mid-on and put in a half-hearted effort there
drops that one short on middle and he ducks under that one well
angling in towards middle, drives it straight towards mid-on
short on middle and he pulls it towards fine leg, kept it low, though was not in total control there
Williamson's dealing in boundaries all of a sudden, superbly done, short of a good length, gets back and punches it square, through point and cover
shortish outside off and he just lets that one go through
Peterson slips-up at mid-off this time, pitched up and Williamson drives that clean, just wide of mid-off, Peterson ends up diving over the ball, four more
pushed that full outside off and it was driven straight to extra cover
drops it short on middle, swivelled at tried to get it fine but couldn't connect that one
shortish outside off, cracks that towards point from the crease
shortish outside off and Elliott runs that down to third man for a single
slower one bowled full outside off and that's defended to cover
shortish outside leg stump, tries to pull it fine, misses, but it's wide enough
shortish outside off, runs that past point for a single into the deep
shortish outside off and he finds the gap, cuts that well past point to pierce that through deep point and third man, nicely played
knocked away into the leg side off the back foot from the crease
tossed up on middle, clips it behind square into the deep for a single
angling in towards middle, comes down the track and drives it towards long-off for a single
angling in towards middle, reaches forward and plays it back down the pitch
slightly short on the off, tapped away into the off side
angling in past leg, tries to force it past midwicket but misses, struck on the back pad
drives that past a diving extra cover into the deep for a single
shortish outside off, chops that towards point from the crease
floating it on leg stump, flicked straight to square leg
fullish outside off and it's driven straight to extra cover
short on middle and it's pulled wide of deep square leg for a couple of runs
sliding it straight, has a big lunge and defends it back to the bowler
ooh, was in the air but managed to evade extra cover, tossed up and Elliott struck that over that fielder to find the gap in the deep and beat Graeme Smith to the boundary
flighted on the off, reaches forward and pushes it towards mid-on for a single
ooh, tried to open the face there with a slip in place, got the edge as it spun away and it fell short of slip
tries to open the face again, gets an inside edge onto the pads
reaches forward and punches that towards extra cover
drives it inside out through extra cover into the deep for a single

goes over the top and places it well, came down the track did Williamson and carted it over midwicket, had picked his spot and found the gap, brings up his half-century in style, good hand from Williamson here
slightly quicker through the air, pushed it back to the bowler
shortish on middle, crunched off the back foot towards extra cover who dives to his left and saves the single
drives it past the bowler towards long-off for a single
slides it on the pads, unable to work it away there, dot ball
didn't spin, quicker, flatter, went on straight, short outside off and he tried to cut but missed
slowed it up, pushed it uppishly past the bowler towards long-off for a single
shortish on middle, pulls it straight to square leg
shortish outside off, cut into the deep for a single
flighted on the off, plays that straight to extra cover from the crease
angling in towards middle, knocked just wide of cover for a single
shortish on the off, pushed straight to extra cover
angling in towards leg stump, worked away into the deep for a single
long hop from Faf, bad ball and well dealt with, thrashes it through square leg, beats deep square leg and deep midwicket
slides it straight on middle, gets back and across and plays it back to the bowler
poor ball again, four more, Williamson picks up his 11th boundary, rocks back and pulls it hard, past midwicket this time
clips it off the front foot through midwicket for a single, raises the 100 for New Zealand
flighted on middle, drives it towards long-off for a single
fullish on leg stump, drives it through midwicket into the deep for a single
shortish outside off, cracks it through point into the deep for a single
opens the face to dab that in front of point for a single
flighted on middle and leg, turns it towards midwicket from the crease
shortish on middle, punched off the back foot to long-on
looping it on middle, comes down the track and pushes it down the pitch
eases that through point and cover into the deep for a single
slightly short on the off, taps that one towards point from the crease
angling in towards middle and leg, pushes it in the direction of midwicket
smartly done, dropped short at 141kmph, swayed back and just guided it over the keeper, seemed to have time to play that, easily done
a little outside off stump and that's square-driven towards point
nipped back in there, struck high on the pads and would have been sliding down as he came forward
short of a good length, gets forward to defend, gets an inside edge onto the pads
tossed up and that's driven down the ground towards long-off for a single
superbly done, fetched it from outside off and swept it really square, came off the middle and there was no protection in the deep
angling in towards middle, drops that towards point and races off for a single, Ingram fumbled while trying to pick it up
floating it on the off, drives it back to the bowler
flatter on the off, pushed it towards extra cover and set off, a dive and a throw but no trouble for the batsman
square-drives that tossed-up delivery through point into the deep for a single
steps out to Kleinveldt, bowled at 134kmph, short and he tries to pull it past midwicket, ends up mistiming it to mid-on
quicker, at 139kmph, on middle, gets an inside edge onto the pads as he tries to push it through
pitched on a length and that's driven wide of deep extra cover for a couple of runs, Smith runs across and cuts it off
slower one bowled short outside off, guided to third man for a single
bowled it short on middle, rolls his wrists over it and pulls it through square leg into the deep for a single
that's a couple more, straying on the pads and it's clipped fine but Behardien runs across to cut it off
he's been patchy today, and is welcomed, like he was in his first spell, with a boundary, drops one short and Williamson seizes the length early, gets across to pull it hard over midwicket
shortish on the off, gets on the back foot to work it past midwicket for a single
slower one, bowled at 124.8kmph, Elliott didn't pick it and played the pull too early there
tries to smack that over midwicket, wants to target McLaren, came down the track and tried to swipe him over midwicket, missed
full toss on middle, drives it towards long-on for a single
slightly short outside off, punched from the crease past extra cover for a single
shortish outside off, crunched off the back foot past point for a single
steers that full delivery towards third man for a single
slower one bowled short outside off, had to drag it past midwicket to get a couple of runs
slower one bowled short, whipped through square leg into the deep for a single
fullish outside off, drilled wide of deep point into the deep for a single
slower one bowled outside off, runs that down to third man for a single
slightly short on the off, clipped through square leg for a single, they think of a second but wisely decide against it in the end
short and pulled well but deep square leg cuts that one off
short again from McLaren, pulled towards deep square leg again for a single
full outside off, cracked towards deep extra cover for a single
fullish on the off and that's driven straight to mid-off from the crease
slower bouncer and it's called a wide, the umpires reckon it was too high, Williamson missed it
full toss and Williamson will feel he missed out, cracked it straight to deep cover
came down the track and had to adjust to the length as Peterson bowled short, he did well did Williamson, waits for it and runs it behind point for three runs
shortish outside off and he opens the face to the right of point for a single
comes down the track and Peterson slows it up, drags it through midwicket for a single
slightly short outside off, cuts it slightly uppishly towards point
short outside off and played straight to point again
gets forward and stabs that towards cover from the crease
slower one bowled short and Williamson cuts that to point
slower one bowled short and he dispatches that one, pulled away through square leg by Williamson, into the nineties now
mistimes a full toss, almost found mid-off but was fortunate it didn't carry
tries to pull that square, quicker from McLaren, bowled at 140.7kmph, gets the bottom of the bat
well fielded at mid-off, drives it well past mid-off but Morkel dives full length to his left and keeps them to just a couple
dropped it short again and Williamson pulls it straight towards deep square leg for a single
Williamson makes some room there, he's given a short ball and he pulls it straight to midwicket
short and he tries to pull that square but misses, struck on the thigh and they steal a leg-bye
Elliott's turn to make some room now, heaves it towards deep midwicket for just a single in the end
makes room to drive that past mid-off as the bowler tries to chase him, gets an inside edge for a single
gone, he succeeded once in guiding a short ball over the keeper's head, he plays this one off the face as well but can't get it high enough, straight to Quinton de Kock
pitched up on middle, aiming for the yorker, pushed towards mid-on
creamed, pitched up and sat up really well for Williamson, just smacked it through extra cover, beating mid-off to the ropes
pitched up again, drives it straight to mid-off this time
reaches his century, knocks it wide of point and steals a single, that's his third ODI hundred
played away into the leg side off the front foot
pitched on a good length and he pushes it firmly to extra cover from the crease, can't beat the gap this time
pitched on a length and he squeezes this over mid-off, just makes a bit of room and manages to just get it over the in-field on the off side, has enough legs on it to take it to the boundary
shortish on middle and he picks up a single through square leg
knocks that one down from the crease behind point
whips that one from middle towards fine leg for a single
pitches it up on middle and he drives it towards midwicket from the crease
drops in the slower one as he comes down the track, outside off and not wide enough, dot ball
just wide of du Plessis, short outside off and that was cut uppishly, du Plessis dived full length to his right there but couldn't get to it, another four
pushes it towards extra cover for a single
McCullum goes big, takes it from a good length, makes a bit of room and swings it away hard over midwicket for a boundary
picks the slower one and dispatches it over long-off, came down the track and thwacked it over the bowler's head, length ball from Morkel and was in the zone
comes down the track and tries to swing it over square leg, misses, had a big heave at that one
bowled'im, yorker length and McCullum appeared to have made his mind up, came down the track and had another swing at that one, missed and was bowled
short of a good length outside off, gets an inside edge onto the pads as he tries to stab it into the off side
slower one bowled outside off, cracked towards point, can't get it past du Plessis
shortish on the off, moves across and pushes it past midwicket for a single

Quinton de Kock dives full length to his right and snaps that one, clipped something on the way after it pitched outside leg, Aleem Dar thinks its the bat and gives it out but Munro immediately calls for a review. Far from the bat, hit the thigh on the way to the keeper, wonder what Dar was seeing there, nowhere near the bat, hit the thigh
short of a good length, crunched off the back foot towards mid-off
run-out attempt, gets an inside edge onto the pads and he wants the single, is sent back, du Plesss tries to under-arm flick it onto the stumps at the striker's end, Munro was gone had that hit
fullish outside off, tries to force that through extra cover, ends up playing it wide of midwicket for a couple of runs, the Powerplay is done
lovely from Williamson, came down the track and drove it inside out over extra cover for a couple, sweetly timed as well
pulls that hard through square leg for a single
shortish on the off, gets on the back foot and punches it to cover
fullish on the off, drags it towards midwicket, cant get it past him
shortish on the off, slaps it hard but straight to mid-off
slower through the air, dabbed towards midwicket for a single to keep strike
well timed by Munro, Tsotso landed it on a length and he cracked it well down the ground and beat mid-on to the boundary
missed run-out, Munro's had a couple of lives on debut, stabbed it wide of point and pinched a single but would have been out had the throw hit direct, 200 up, gets an extra run on the overtthrow
guides that one from the crease towards point

Munro seemed to be over-eager during his short stay, still 11 overs left in the innings, slower one from Tsotso and Munro seemed to have made up his mind, tried to clear long-on but didn't pick the slower one, Colin Inrgram ran in from the deep and took a well-judged catch diving forward
Williamson tucks that around for a single in the deep
New Zealand are slipping here, some reverse for Tsotso, swung in towards the batsman, pitched on a length and Franklin was half-forward while trying to play, was bowled through the gate
Williamson tries to go over extra cover but ends up spooning that in the direction of long-on, lucky it didn't carry
gets a stride out and defends it into the off side
shortish on the off, gets on the back foot and pushes it through square leg for a single
short on the off and it's slapped back towards the bowler who dives and gets his right hand to it, can't stop the single though
thick outside edge, that's four, comes down the track to drive it through extra cover, ended up slicing it past a vacant point region for a boundary
floating it on the off stump, gets across and pushes it to midwicket
striking it well is Williamson, pitched up outside off and it's driven to mid-off
low full toss outside off, drags it wide of deep midwicket for a couple of runs, well run

run-out, Williamson called out belatedly, yelled out "No", but Neesham was more than halfway down the pitch there, rushed for the single, then sent back, the cramp is playing on his mind, Faf collected it from point and aimed at the non-striker's end, Tsotso got a hand to it on its way to the stumps, Neesham was short
slower one outside off, guides it behind point into the deep for a single
yorker length outside off and he's dug it out in the direction of point
goodish length outside off and he's played it back to the bowler
Williamson moves across and plays it in front of mid-on for a single
sliding on the pads and it's been flicked to the right of fine leg, McCullum rushes back for the second and makes it in time
short of a good length outside off, goes for the cut but misses
shortish on middle, turns it from the crease through square leg for a couple of runs
good, sharp short ball, dropped it outside off and McCullum got out of the way there
slightly short on the off, knocks it down into the off side and races off for a single
pitched on a length and it's pushed back towards the bowler
short of a good length, drops it in front of point and sets off, McLaren gathers and throws but can't get the stumps at the non-striker's end
a bit of width there but went through quickly as Williamson tried to cut, missed
slower one bowled short outside off, cut away to third man for a single
sliding down leg but he moved well across there, not called a wide
slower one bowled short, turned through square leg into the deep for a single
shortish on the off, punched off the back foot to long-off for a single
short outside off, cut towards point from the crease
floating it on middle, comes down the track and pushes it to long-off for a single
shortish on the off, punched through to long-on for a single
short outside off, turns away, cuts it towards Tsttso at point, there's a misfield there
floated it outside off, pushed through cover into the deep for a single
whipped through midwicket for a single
slower one bowled short outside off, tries to pull it square, misses
full toss and is well dealt, punched over mid-on for a boundary, easily done by McCullum
leading edge but safe, slower one and he closes the face too early, gets a leading edge and just over McLaren's head, lands just behind the stumps at the non-striker's end
full toss, pushed through to long-on for a single
slower one bowled short, pulled towards deep square leg for a single
that's not going to help, slower ball gone bad, too wide outside off
goodish length on middle, pushes it towards long-on for a single
full on middle, aiming for the yorker, dug out towards long-on for a single
slides down leg, tries to glance it fine, misses, strikes the pads, they get a leg-bye
low full toss on leg stump, driven straight to midwicket, just the single
bowled it full on middle, drives it wide of long-on for a single, err, there's a fumble and they're back for the second
missed run-out, pushed through to extra cover and they try a suicidal single, the fielder aims and misses, Williamson was gone had that hit
gets across and whips it through square leg into the deep for a single
trying to scoop it past fine leg, struck on the pads outside the line, they get a leg-bye
shortish on the off and Williamson is in pain again, tries to pull it square and he's struggling while trying to take the single
makes a bit of room and the bowler follows him, clips it uppishly and straight to midwicket where Tsotso takes it comfortably
poor delivery, way down the leg side, Mills had four if he got his bat to it, gets a wide in the end
short of a good length, knocks it down in front of off and takes off for a single
slower one, pushes it towards midwicket to keep the strike
yorker length on middle, manages to dig it out to the bowler, good stuff
length ball and he picks it up well, swings it over midwicket and gets a boundary for his efforts
strikes it towards long-on this time, wanted the second but it wasn't on
yorker length on middle, punches it wide of midwicket in the deep this time for a couple of runs
drops that short on middle, tries to pull it square, pinches a single, took the bottom of the bat
full outside off and he finds the gap through the off side, cracks it through the covers, had to stretch in the end but connected well, more through cover and point there
full toss and he's mistimed it to midwicket, for a single
short on the off and he pulls it to midwicket, Tsotso takes aim and misses at the non-striker's end, missed run-out
short and that's maximum, goes for a mighty pull, gets a top-edge, gets the desired result, over the keeper and over the fine-leg boundary
handy runs these, short of a good length, he makes room and swings it away over midwicket for a one bounce four, connected well
almost yorker length there, he can only push it to mid-off for a single
length, length and it's been dispatched over long-on, long-on got a hand to that one, Ingram was the man there but couldn't quite hold on, that's struck over the man there, just about, for a six

inn2.comm: good length on the off, rocks forward and guides it towards point from the crease
sliding down leg there, big appeal but that would have missed leg, Quinton moved across to flick that one square
beaten, caught walking on that one, pitched on a length outside off, rocked forward to drive it through the line, it moved across to beat the outside edge
strikes it across the line but does it well, pitched on a length and he cracks it wide of mid-on for three runs
short of a length on the off, punched off the back foot towards mid-on
beaten, lovely delivery, pitching on a good length and just moving away to go past the outside edge as he rocks forward to push at that one
pitched up on middle and leg and he drives it through towards mid-on
fullish on the off and he's pushed it towards mid-off, didn't move his feet much
a touch too wide there from the left-arm seamer, called a wide by the umpire
short of a length and that's cut straight towards point from the crease
pitched on a length and he leans forward to drive that between extra cover and mid-off for a few runs, nicely timed by de Kock
turns the face to that straightish delivery, slightly short on middle and it's played to midwicket
shortish on middle, turned through square leg for a single
superbly fielded at extra cover by Nathan McCullum, pitched up and de Kock drilled it but McCullum dived to his left to stop that, saved a certain four
bowling it on a driving length outside off, pushed towards mid-off from the crease
short of a good length outside off, chops it down behind point for a single
on middle and off, Smith moved across and tried to turn the face to whip that past midwicket, got a leading edge but it went along the ground
shortish on middle, turned through square leg for a single
shortish outside off and he's chopped that down towards point
pitches it on a length on middle and he's driven that well, but straight to mid-on
goodish length on the off, rocks forward and plays that solidly to cover
full toss outside off and Smith misses out, mistimes that one to mid-off
struck high on the pads, bowled slightly short on leg as he tried to turn it square
gets forward and turns that one wide of mid-on for a single
shortish outside off, bowled at 135.3kmph, tries to chop it behind point, just goes past the outside edge
slightly short on the off, gets across and punches it towards mid-on from the crease
slightly short, gets across and punches it towards midwicket, that's his strength but can't get it past the fielder
shortish outside off, tries to slap it past extra cover, the fielder gets a hand to it, palms it towards mid-off and they take a single
crunched into the off side off the front foot
pushed it full on the off and that's struck straight towards mid-off
wonder what Mills is appealing for there, it landed a mile outside leg stump and probably not even have gone on to hit leg
pitched up on the off, gets across and plays it wide of mid-on for a single
drives it clean off the front foot, bowled at 133.7kmph, on a good length but he can't get that one past mid-off
superb hit, picked it up beautifully from the off stump, got across and smashed it over midwicket for a six, lovely clean strike
